text: Plounéour-Trez () is a former commune. It is found in the region Brittany in the Finistère department in the northwest of France. On 1 January 2017, it was merged into the new commune of Plounéour-Brignogan-Plages.Arrêté préfectoral 29 June 2016 == References == Category:Former communes in Finistère
title: Plounéour-Trez
